 Here, as the lower figure in Fig \ref{fig:4}  shows, the NJL operator generates a mass no matter how small the NJL operator is (this is because there is already a condensate present due to $B$). As the NJL operator coupling is increased the mass grows. This is consistent with gap equation analysis of chiral symmetry breaking theories enhanced by NJL operators (see for example \cite{King:1990hd}). 

